    "name": "Teddy Wilson",
    "profile": "American jazz pianist.\r\nBorn November 24, 1912, Austin, Texas, USA.\r\nDied July 31, 1986, New Britain, Connecticut, USA.\r\n\r\nDescribed by jazz critic [a=Scott Yanow] as \"the definitive swing pianist.\" \r\nWilson's sophisticated and elegant style was featured on the records of many of the biggest names in jazz including [a38201], [a300050], [a254768], [a33589], and [a31615]. With Goodman, he was perhaps the first well-known black musician to play publicly in a racially integrated group. In addition to his extensive work as a sideman, Wilson also led his own groups and recording sessions from the late 1920s until the 1980s.\r\nBrother of [a=Augustus Wilson]. Briefly married to songwriter [a=Irene Wilson] in the 1930s.",
